      • isValidCore

        protected boolean isValidCore(CycObject cycObject)
                       throws KBApiRuntimeException,
                              KBApiServerSideException
        This not part of the public, supported KB API. Check that the candidate core object is valid for this type. This is part of the bootstrapping process, where we check the core before we build a KB Object. At this point, we can not use any KB API methods or KBObjectImpl.getCore(). This checks the validity of only KBTerm subclasses. The core validity for Assertion and its subclasses, Sentence, Variable and Symbol are handled by the individual classes If a Variable is wrapped by any subclass of KBTerm, then it is always considered valid core. This is to allow representing a #$CycLDenotationalTerm and #$CycLVariable of a given type (#$Collection) using same KBTerm subclass.
        Parameters:
        cycObject - the object that is checked for type given by getTypeString()
        Returns:
        if a cycObject is of a given type
        Throws:
        KBApiRuntimeException - if there is a problem connecting to Cyc
        KBApiServerSideException - if there is problem executing a SubL command NOTE: This does not throw KBTypeException just because there is a server error.
